    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Madam—</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I am sorry to say that I can not spare the time to discuss the many abstruse points touched on in your letter.— Nor do I understand fully on what subject you require information.— I may add that my belief is not nearly so <hi rend="italic">[</hi>sure<hi rend="italic">]</hi>, as you suppose<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Madam | your obed sert | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.1 can] <hi rend="italic">interl above del</hi> ‘have’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.1 spare the] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.2 fully on] ‘on’ <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n4">1.2 subject] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘you’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n5">1.3 my] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘I do not’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n6">1.3 belief] <hi rend="italic">altered from</hi> ‘believe’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n7">1.3 is not] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n8">1.3 <hi rend="italic">[</hi>sure<hi rend="italic">]</hi>] <hi rend="italic">after del illeg</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
